full_summary:
---

Government Tender Announcement
==========================

### Overview

The Department of Fisheries and Oceans (DFO) is seeking a commercially available SaaS Cloud-based Enterprise Incident Response Management System for 200 concurrent users, with the potential to expand to 100-200 additional users within the next three years.

**Contract Details**

*   **Reference number:** WS3597350006-Doc4087350864
*   **Solicitation number:** WS3597350006
*   **Publication date:** July 12, 2023
*   **Closing date:** September 6, 2023, at 14:00:00
*   **Expected contract start date:** March 1, 2024
*   **Expected contract end date:** December 1, 2024

**Trade Agreements**

This procurement is subject to the following trade agreements:

*   Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
*   Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)
*   Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement
*   Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
*   World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA)
*   Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA)
*   Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement
*   Canada-UK Trade Continuity Agreement (Canada-UK TCA)
*   Canada-Ukraine Free Trade Agreement (CUFTA)

**Procurement Method**

This procurement will be conducted using a competitive, open bidding process.

**Notice Type**

*   Notice Type: Request for Proposal
*   Notice Type (French): Demande de propositions

**Request for Tender**

DFO requires a commercially available SaaS Cloud-based Enterprise Incident Response Management System for the following requirements:

*   200 concurrent users
*   24-month warranty
*   Software maintenance and support
*   Documentation
*   Training
*   Optional professional services

The requested solution must be provided by a supplier that can meet the following criteria:

*   The product must be able to scale to accommodate up to 300 users.
*   The supplier must provide ongoing maintenance and support for the system.
*   The supplier must provide documentation for the system.
*   The supplier must provide training on the system.

**Additional Information**

For further details, please refer to the notice document and attachments available on the Ariba Discovery website at [http://discovery.ariba.com/rfx/16805980](http://discovery.ariba.com/rfx/
